<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 2:23PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Scattered snow showers and lightning this afternoon...
Scattered snow showers will continue to move from west to east
across the region this afternoon. Some of the snow showers could
be heavy at times, especially in the Loma and Fort Benton areas.
Visibility will fall below one mile at times, especially in
heavier snow showers.
New snow accumulations this afternoon will mostly be on grassy
areas and generally less than one inch.
Additionally a few lightning strikes are also possible. Reminder,
if you hear thunder, go inside until the storm passes.</description>
